\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering DTR in constructor**\\n\\nI'm thinking about whether I need to build and also initialize DTR in the constructor before I set the TCCL. It seems important to verify the order of operations here. If DTR needs to be configured first, that could impact how the TCCL is established later on. So, I'll need to ensure that everything is sequenced correctly to avoid any potential issues later in the process. Alright, let’s dig into this and make sure I get it right!\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering test dependencies**\\n\\nI'm thinking about whether I should add a test dependency for JAXB, especially since I'm working with Java 21. It's interesting how dependencies can really affect the project setup. I wonder if there's a specific version I should look for or if there are any best practices to follow. I'll have to dig deeper into how JAXB integrates with Java 21 and what options I have for my project.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering JAXB Dependencies**\\n\\nI'm figuring out how to compile a project that uses JAXB while running on Java 21 since JAXB is missing in Java 9+. It seems like the project currently doesn't have JAXB on the test classpath, which is causing issues with referencing JAXB classes. I think I need to add dependencies for both the test and runtime to support XML configuration on the modern JDK. I’ll explore whether the hibernate-validator POM includes optional JAXB dependencies.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Exploring JAXB and API Use**\\n\\nI need XML for Java 21 tests, but adding JAXB alongside might complicate things with native metadata. It might be better to avoid XML if I handle internal paths directly. There are two call sites needing an internal path, and I could use `ValidationBootstrapParameters` with a custom `BootstrapConfiguration` that doesn't rely on JAXB, but that's still internal. I wonder if this is considered \\\"normal public API\\\"? It seems like I need to check if other versions include JAXB in their test dependencies.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_cvrnf6SwswWR632IL4FwLrB1|fc_05fe7b53bdd6e841016a283e4c7bd08196bab12ce62c954d50", "name": "bash", "arguments": {"command": "rg \"jaxb|glassfish.jaxb|javax.xml.bind\" tests/src -n | head -50"}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 394, "output": 1466, "cacheRead": 36864, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 38724, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1781022244811, "responseId": "resp_05fe7b53bdd6e841016a283e254a1c8196af11034685f13255"}, "toolResults": [{"role": "toolResult", "toolCallId": "call_cvrnf6SwswWR632IL4FwLrB1|fc_05fe7b53bdd6e841016a283e4c7bd08196bab12ce62c954d50", "toolName": "bash", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "tests/src/org.ehcache/ehcache/3.10.8-jakarta/src/test/resources/META-INF/native-image/reachability-metadata.json:10:          \"org.glassfish.jaxb.core.v2.model.annotation.Locatable\"\ntests/src/org.ehcache/ehcache/3.10.8-jakarta/src/test/resources/META-INF/native-image/reachability-metadata.json:21:          \"org.glassfish.jaxb.core.v2.model.annotation.Locatable\"\ntests/src/org.ehcache/ehcache/3.10.8-jakarta/src/test/resources/META-INF/native-image/reachability-metadata.json:32:          \"org.glassfish.jaxb.core.v2.model.annotation.Locatable\"\ntests/src/org.ehcache/ehcache/3.10.8-jakarta/src/test/resources/META-INF/native-image/reachability-metadata.json:43:          \"org.glassfish.jaxb.core.v2.model.annotation.Locatable\"\ntests/src/org.ehcache/ehcache/3.10.8-jakarta/src/test/resources/META-INF/native-image/reachability-metadata.json:54:          \"org.glassfish.jaxb.core.v2.model.annotation.Locatable\"\ntests/src/org.ehcache/ehcache/3.10.8-jakarta/src/test/resources/META-INF/native-image/reachability-metadata.json:65:          \"org.glassfish.jaxb.core.v2.model.annotation.Locata