 to be final? Well, existing projects seem to follow different practices regarding final variables. I also need to verify if `ValidatorFactory.close()` is available in Bean Validation 1.1. It's looking like it is!\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Examining XML and JAXB dependencies**\\n\\nI'm digging into a potential issue with my XML parser needing a specific order for element names along with an optional default-provider before the message-interpolator. I’ve identified that my XML setup meets this requirement. I'm also checking if my JAXB dependency (`jaxb-runtime:2.3.9`) pulls in `jakarta.activation-api`. There’s a bit of confusion because after JavaEE was renamed, `jakarta.xml.bind-api` still uses the javax package. It's fine not to include certain compile dependencies. I’ll also consider untracked metadata and dependencies for coverage improvements before finalizing the project.\"}]}"}, {"type": "text", "text": "Implemented focused coverage for `org.hibernate.validator.internal.util.privilegedactions.LoadClass`.\n\nChanged files:\n- `tests/src/org.hibernate/hibernate-validator/5.2.4.Final/src/test/java/org_hibernate/hibernate_validator/LoadClassTest.java`\n  - Added a dedicated public `LoadClassTest`.\n  - Exercises Hibernate Validator XML bootstrap paths that reach:\n    - HV namespace successful load\n    - HV namespace TCCL fallback failure path\n    - external classloader load\n    - TCCL load\n    - fallback to Hibernate Validator classloader\n  - Uses Bean Validation/Hibernate Validator bootstrap APIs rather than direct reflection.\n- `tests/src/org.hibernate/hibernate-validator/5.2.4.Final/build.gradle`\n  - Added JAXB API/runtime test dependencies needed for `validation.xml` parsing on modern JDKs.\n\nI did not run compile/tests, per instruction.", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_05fe7b53bdd6e841016a283f16c6c48196ad1836d156cbf0e9\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "us